Description: repo context maps for AI coding agents (Agentic Harness Standard)
 ATLAS gives AI coding agents a small, maintained set of Markdown files to read
 before they work, instead of re-scanning the whole repository every session:
 .
  * ATLAS.md   — where everything lives (the repository map)
  * SKILL.md   — procedural playbook + known failure modes (stable anchors)
  * CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md — the behavioral contract for coding agents
 .
 It ships a zero-dependency CLI (init, check, measure, doctor, export, anchors,
 adr, research, and more) plus adapters for Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, Gemini,
 Zed, GitHub Copilot, OpenCode, Hermes, and a generic runtime. ATLAS is a
 complement to AGENTS.md, not a replacement: `atlas export` regenerates the
 per-runtime files from one canonical source.
